{% from "macros/code_preview.njk" import code_preview %}
{% from "macros/code_block.njk" import code_block %}
{% from "components/dialog.njk" import dialog %}

<div class="alert mb-6">
  {% lucide "info" %}
  <h2>The Alert Dialog component uses the <a href="/components/dialog" class="font-medium underline underline-offset-4">Dialog</a> component.</h2>
</div>

{% set code %}{% set footer %}
  <button class="btn-outline" @click="open = false">Cancel</button>
  <button class="btn-primary" @click="open = false">Continue</button>
{% endset %}
{{ dialog(
  id="demo-alert-dialog",
  title="Are you absolutely sure?",
  description="This action cannot be undone. This will permanently delete your account and remove your data from our servers.",
  trigger="Open Alert Dialog",
  trigger_attrs={"class": "btn-outline"},
  footer=footer,
  close_button=false,
  close_on_overlay_click=false
) }}{% endset %}
{{ code_preview("alert-dialog", code | prettyHtml) }}

<h2 id="usage"><a href="#usage">Usage</a></h2>

<h3 id="usage-default"><a href="#usage-default">Default</a></h3>

<section class="prose my-6">
  <p>The Alert Dialog component uses the same Alpine.js code as the <a href="/components/dialog" class="font-medium underline underline-offset-4">Dialog</a> component with one small difference: we set <code>initialCloseOnOverlayClick</code> to <code>false</code> to prevent the dialog from closing when the overlay is clicked.</p>
</section>

{{ code_block(code | prettyHtml) }}

<h3 id="usage-jinja"><a href="#usage-jinja">Jinja or Nunjucks</a></h3>

<section class="prose my-6">
  <p>If you use Jinja (or Nunjucks), you can use the <code>dialog()</code> macro directly, making sure to set <code>close_on_overlay_click</code> to <code>False</code> (or <code>false</code> for Nunjucks).</p>
